  "body": "### Version Information\r\n\r\n* vyper Version (output of `vyper --version`): 0.1.0b9\r\n* OS: OS X\r\n* Python Version (output of `python --version`): 3.7\r\n* Environment (output of `pip freeze`):\r\n\r\n### What's your issue about?\r\n\r\nThe following contract:\r\n\r\n```\r\nholdings: public(uint256)\r\n\r\n@private\r\ndef getHoldings() -> uint256:\r\n    return self.holdings\r\n\r\n@public\r\ndef getZero() -> uint256:\r\n    token_reserve: uint256 = self.extBalanceOf()\r\n    return 0\r\n```\r\n\r\nCompiles to blocks that include dynamic jump statements:\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/224585/58253128-9f54a300-7d5f-11e9-98ed-ad5afa10c7f1.png)\r\n\r\nIn this case the jump destination originates in memory.\r\n\r\nAs a result Vyper bytecode is much harder to analyze using static analysis/formal verification techniques, which could limit assurances for Vyper contracts\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed?\r\n\r\n-\r\n",
