    "body": "To elaborate on what @fubuloubu said - we use dynamic jumps because of how we use copying of parameters, and copying of existing function context to the stack when making a private call. \r\n\r\nConsidering that - there is no way we can statically determine where a function must jump back to on `return` ie. could be called from more than one function.",
